name: Tyrone GRANT, Petitioner v. PHILADELPHIA COUNTY COURT OF COMMON PLEAS, Respondent
name_abbreviation: Grant v. Philadelphia County Court of Common Pleas

parties: Tyrone GRANT, Petitioner v. PHILADELPHIA COUNTY COURT OF COMMON PLEAS, Respondent.

opinions.text:
ORDER
PER CURIAM.
AND NOW, this 6th day of October, 2010, the Application for Leave to File Original Process and the Petition for Writ of Mandamus and/or Extraordinary Relief are GRANTED. The Court of Common Pleas of Philadelphia County shall dispose of Petitioner’s Post Conviction Relief Act Petition within 90 days of this order.
opinions.author: PER CURIAM.
